[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:30,740 --> 00:00:35,960
[Oh No! Here Comes Trouble]

3
00:00:36,130 --> 00:00:40,430
[Episode 9]

4
00:00:38,590 --> 00:00:39,420
Come on, report.

5
00:00:40,020 --> 00:00:41,480
Guangyan, have you succeeded in hitting on Lin Xin?

6
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:44,100
Actually, she hit on me first.

7
00:00:47,710 --> 00:00:49,290
[Hello]

8
00:00:58,350 --> 00:00:59,850
I guess I was right to send the best-looking guy.

9
00:01:00,660 --> 00:01:01,110
No, it's not like that.

10
00:01:01,740 --> 00:01:03,320
-It's because I'm a medical student. -All right.

11
00:01:03,350 --> 00:01:04,790
I know you're good-looking and talented, so stop showing off.

12
00:01:05,620 --> 00:01:06,680
Did you get anything?

13
00:01:07,220 --> 00:01:08,700
[Are you a medical student?]

14
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:17,500
[Can I ask you a question?]

15
00:01:16,970 --> 00:01:18,480
I didn't want to ask too many questions at our first meeting.

16
00:01:18,930 --> 00:01:20,120
I'll see her tomorrow.

17
00:01:20,580 --> 00:01:21,100
That's good.

18
00:01:21,860 --> 00:01:22,250
And you?

19
00:01:23,890 --> 00:01:24,890
Have you had dinner?

20
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,100
Yes, thanks.

21
00:01:26,390 --> 00:01:27,039
I have too.

22
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:29,020
Who cares?

23
00:01:29,580 --> 00:01:30,420
I haven't yet.

24
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:32,160
I've been sitting over there all day.

25
00:01:32,410 --> 00:01:33,100
The clerk kept looking at me.

26
00:01:33,100 --> 00:01:34,560
I had to keep refilling the cheapest coffee.

27
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:36,330
Now that I've spent all my money,

28
00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:37,420
I haven't had a single grain of rice.

29
00:01:47,830 --> 00:01:49,250
I thought you said you'd buy steak or beef noodles.

30
00:01:50,860 --> 00:01:51,710
What's the situation?

31
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:53,200
I've been watching it all day.

32
00:01:56,590 --> 00:01:58,450
The oldest woman must be Lin Jingmei, right?

33
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,740
So you stayed there all day

34
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,110
just to tell if the woman was Lin Jingmei?

35
00:02:02,570 --> 00:02:03,690
Don't you have a photo?

36
00:02:03,780 --> 00:02:04,890
It was shot seven years ago.

37
00:02:04,970 --> 00:02:05,610
Who knows

38
00:02:05,610 --> 00:02:07,160
if she's gotten fatter, thinner, older, or younger.

39
00:02:07,680 --> 00:02:08,120
No.

40
00:02:08,139 --> 00:02:08,810
Nothing strange

41
00:02:09,979 --> 00:02:10,979
leaned over

42
00:02:10,979 --> 00:02:12,410
and told you the secret of Lin Jingmei?

43
00:02:14,130 --> 00:02:15,240
He didn't bring a brush.

44
00:02:21,190 --> 00:02:22,050
You should bring your four treasures of the study

45
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:23,320
here for another day.

46
00:02:23,420 --> 00:02:24,500
You can drink coffee while you write.

47
00:02:24,850 --> 00:02:25,460
Remember to

48
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:26,620
attract something strange.

49
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:27,820
Right.

50
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,230
Maybe those teapots, cups, and creamer balls

51
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:31,600
will tell me Lin Jingmei's secret.

52
00:02:32,860 --> 00:02:33,770
What do you take me for?

53
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:36,410
It's hard to say.

54
00:02:36,430 --> 00:02:37,900
The sidewalk came to see you.

55
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:42,340
There is something weird.

56
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:45,810
The coffee shop.

57
00:02:47,490 --> 00:02:48,010
Where?

58
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:49,940
It's the coffee shop.

59
00:02:50,930 --> 00:02:51,780
The shop itself?

60
00:02:51,890 --> 00:02:52,670
What's weird about it?

61
00:02:53,020 --> 00:02:54,329
I've been sitting there all day.

62
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,340
The longer I sat there, the more I felt something strange.

63
00:02:58,380 --> 00:02:59,030
Chuying.

64
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,910
I think you said something similar yesterday.

65
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:04,490
It's when Zhao Baisi and Xie Hui

66
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,570
were talking,

67
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,800
I felt that there was something wrong.

68
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:09,920
Something wrong?

69
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,470
But they said the truth and didn't lie.

70
00:03:18,890 --> 00:03:20,010
So...

71
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,480
Is there any news about He'an?

72
00:03:23,700 --> 00:03:25,370
We're just re-reading the information

73
00:03:25,530 --> 00:03:26,780
for a potential new clue.

74
00:03:46,740 --> 00:03:48,010
Your colleague called you a few times.

75
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:48,770
You didn't hear them.

76
00:03:50,060 --> 00:03:50,540
But

77
00:03:50,829 --> 00:03:51,740
what does “one-per” mean?

78
00:03:54,220 --> 00:03:55,240
Nothing. Stop asking around.

79
00:03:58,470 --> 00:03:59,740
I shouldn't have come here by myself,

80
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:01,110
right?

81
00:04:01,860 --> 00:04:02,720
The director warned me

82
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:04,570
that I couldn't have outsiders in the office anymore.

83
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,470
Unless you're a suspect.

84
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:12,600
What can I do for you?

85
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:15,760
This is for you.

86
00:04:16,329 --> 00:04:17,060
Again?

87
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:22,570
No.

88
00:04:23,060 --> 00:04:25,100
I didn't mean it was too sweet.

89
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:26,760
It's because a friend of mine who studied medicine said

90
00:04:26,780 --> 00:04:27,280
too much sugar

91
00:04:27,310 --> 00:04:29,520
can damage the brain and weaken cognitive ability.

92
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:29,900
So...

93
00:04:29,920 --> 00:04:30,600
I'm sorry

94
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:32,250
for causing damage to your brain.

95
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:42,690
It's strange how someone can write calligraphy here.

96
00:04:45,360 --> 00:04:47,180
If it doesn't work, you're going down.

97
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:55,240
What should I write?

98
00:04:57,170 --> 00:04:58,470
No matter how hard I try to focus on their conversation,

99
00:04:58,490 --> 00:04:59,720
I still can't figure it out.

100
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:01,480
So I need brain power now.

101
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:02,630
I don't want to eat anything sweet for now.

102
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:03,710
For now.

103
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:04,870
That's it.

104
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:08,930
Can I listen to it?

105
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:11,740
The recording.

106
00:05:12,070 --> 00:05:12,790
No, you can't.

107
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,140
I'm sorry.

108
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:17,530
I was wrong again.

109
00:05:18,030 --> 00:05:18,570
Wrong about what?

110
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,720
You're an outsider and you don't know the rules of the police.

111
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,230
An outsider?

112
00:05:27,810 --> 00:05:28,430
Okay, listen to it.

113
00:05:28,690 --> 00:05:29,670
No.

114
00:05:29,940 --> 00:05:31,660
I just mentioned it without thinking.

115
00:05:31,690 --> 00:05:32,560
Don't be so nosy.

116
00:05:33,010 --> 00:05:34,320
You don't know anyone in the recording.

117
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:35,320
It's better to judge by feeling.

118
00:05:46,270 --> 00:05:47,890
I'm just an ordinary person,

119
00:05:48,220 --> 00:05:48,960
not as good as the police.

120
00:05:49,090 --> 00:05:49,570
I know.

121
00:05:50,990 --> 00:05:52,070
But there is something

122
00:05:52,990 --> 00:05:54,830
I'm not sure whether I should call it strange or not.

123
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:55,570
Tell me about it.

124
00:05:56,050 --> 00:05:57,020
But I'm just an ordinary…

125
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,470
Ordinary people. I know.

126
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:58,980
Say it.

127
00:06:00,290 --> 00:06:01,650
Mr. Zhao

128
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:04,090
reminds me of my elementary school tutor.

129
00:06:05,450 --> 00:06:07,500
That tutor was usually very indifferent to me.

130
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,980
But whenever my parents came to school,

131
00:06:10,280 --> 00:06:11,920
she would keep calling my name

132
00:06:11,970 --> 00:06:13,100
in front of them,

133
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:16,020
as if the more times she called my name,

134
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,730
the more she cared for me.

135
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:20,750
And?

136
00:06:22,500 --> 00:06:23,520
If it were me,

137
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,260
I wouldn't

138
00:06:26,730 --> 00:06:27,910
keep mentioning the kid's name.

139
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:29,520
Why?

140
00:06:30,510 --> 00:06:32,150
Since it's related to the police,

141
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:33,950
something must have happened

142
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:35,760
to the kid.

143
00:06:42,450 --> 00:06:44,409
My brother died when I was a teenager.

144
00:06:45,780 --> 00:06:46,510
Not to mention me,

145
00:06:47,610 --> 00:06:49,210
even my parents tried not to

146
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:50,740
mention his name in front of each other,

147
00:06:52,050 --> 00:06:53,800
even when discussing him.

148
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,730
But as for Mr. Zhao,

149
00:06:59,890 --> 00:07:02,250
the child's father was right next to him but he kept…

150
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:06,560
But maybe my family is strange.

151
00:07:12,540 --> 00:07:13,450
Or maybe

152
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:15,180
Mr. Zhao

153
00:07:15,710 --> 00:07:16,360
values personal feelings

154
00:07:17,390 --> 00:07:18,100
and is very emotional.

155
00:07:20,210 --> 00:07:21,340
If that's the case,

156
00:07:21,820 --> 00:07:23,850
Mr. and Mrs. Xie Hui were his and his wife's introducers.

157
00:07:23,890 --> 00:07:25,010
He would have mentioned this.

158
00:07:26,520 --> 00:07:27,590
But he only mentioned

159
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:29,650
Xie Hui's help at work.

160
00:07:35,470 --> 00:07:36,030
Thank you for that.

161
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:36,659
I'll have to…

162
00:07:37,610 --> 00:07:38,090
Wait a minute.

163
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:39,140
So this…

164
00:07:41,470 --> 00:07:42,040
I'll take it to

165
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:42,909
a friend who has a bad brain.

166
00:07:42,909 --> 00:07:43,290
Thank you.

167
00:07:46,580 --> 00:07:46,990
Okay.

168
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,210
I don't know.

169
00:07:49,210 --> 00:07:50,080
Just put your heart into it.

170
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,050
Write a few words.

171
00:07:51,730 --> 00:07:53,210
Senior, yes, please take a look.

172
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,400
-So Cao… -I can't talk on the phone right now.

173
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,250
Anyway, if you put your mind to it, you'll have power.

174
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,480
You can write whatever you like.

175
00:08:06,030 --> 00:08:07,680
I just have to put my heart into it, right?

176
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:23,230
[Chen Chuying, Cao Guangyan, go eat shit]

177
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,010
Are you human?

178
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:33,520
I'm sorry.

179
00:08:34,179 --> 00:08:35,980
I've told you many times before.

180
00:08:36,330 --> 00:08:37,270
We're closing now.

181
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,410
This better works.

182
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:46,670
They just keep asking me to write.

183
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,140
Well.

184
00:09:06,820 --> 00:09:07,910
Can you turn off the lights again?

185
00:09:09,090 --> 00:09:10,210
We're closed.

186
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:12,310
Please check your things.

187
00:09:12,350 --> 00:09:13,360
Don't forget to take it with you.

188
00:10:14,450 --> 00:10:15,970
I love you so much.

189
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:25,470
Come out.

190
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:29,190
Come on out.

191
00:10:31,050 --> 00:10:32,180
He's cursing again.

192
00:10:47,790 --> 00:10:48,400
No way.

193
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:50,730
What?

194
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,640
It's not going to kill you.

195
00:10:52,070 --> 00:10:53,630
Do you want to scare the woman to death?

196
00:10:56,470 --> 00:10:57,010
Ms. He?

197
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,310
I don't care about her.

198
00:11:01,050 --> 00:11:01,820
I'm afraid she'll think

199
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:03,480
someone's trying to steal her baby doll

200
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:05,400
and she'll hug me and cry again.

201
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:06,720
It's so annoying.

202
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:08,640
I didn't ask you.

203
00:11:09,310 --> 00:11:10,020
Come with me to a place.

204
00:11:10,460 --> 00:11:11,120
Where to?

205
00:11:13,790 --> 00:11:14,450
You believe

206
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:16,010
what I just said, right?

207
00:11:17,730 --> 00:11:19,710
It's true. I don't care about the woman.

208
00:11:20,580 --> 00:11:23,580
So you had four interviews in the first place?

209
00:11:25,710 --> 00:11:27,430
Your grades don't sound like a problem.

210
00:11:27,710 --> 00:11:28,530
Don't be so anxious.

211
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:31,250
I have no problem with

212
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:32,650
the written test and the run-through you just mentioned.

213
00:11:33,140 --> 00:11:35,230
But my PBL sucks.

214
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:37,970
Just remember that during the group discussion,

215
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,350
don't just say whatever comes to mind.

216
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,270
Wait a few seconds to organize the argument before speaking.

217
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,610
It's better to somehow manage to be

218
00:11:44,650 --> 00:11:46,060
the leader of the group.

219
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:49,620
It's hard.

220
00:11:52,660 --> 00:11:54,020
Why do you want to go to medical school?

221
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:56,940
Are any of your parents doctors?

222
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,970
Anyway, the bottom line of the test is

223
00:12:08,970 --> 00:12:10,370
not to keep silent,

224
00:12:10,790 --> 00:12:12,230
or try to steal the show.

225
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:13,560
You'll give the professor a bad impression.

226
00:12:13,780 --> 00:12:15,650
Because it's the best way to show off.

227
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:20,200
I thought you just taught me

228
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:22,710
to wait a few seconds to think about my answer.

229
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:26,170
You really thought about your answer?

230
00:12:29,580 --> 00:12:30,700
It's my mom.

231
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:31,970
Your mom?

232
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:33,520
Actually,

233
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:36,300
it doesn't matter where I get into.

234
00:12:37,100 --> 00:12:38,190
I just think

235
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:39,840
as long as I get into medical school,

236
00:12:41,180 --> 00:12:41,930
my mom

237
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,400
won't compare me with others anymore.

238
00:12:44,490 --> 00:12:45,820
That's why I'm saying this.

239
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,510
Don't say that to the professor

240
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:54,060
in the interview.

241
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:07,550
Why would the cop and the medical student

242
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:09,230
hang out with people like you?

243
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:11,540
What's wrong with me?

244
00:13:13,010 --> 00:13:13,970
Are you watching?

245
00:13:14,260 --> 00:13:15,110
Remind me if someone's passing by.

246
00:13:41,090 --> 00:13:42,240
Is it like what I said?

247
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,650
So disgusting.

248
00:14:01,030 --> 00:14:01,910
The apron is the same,

249
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:17,510
only in a different color.

250
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:19,610
This is exactly the same as Ms. He's shop.

251
00:14:22,730 --> 00:14:23,580
Pervert.

252
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:28,260
Could that woman's kid be here too?

253
00:14:29,010 --> 00:14:30,760
What do you mean? Whose kid?

254
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:33,560
Can't you see it here?

255
00:14:34,660 --> 00:14:35,640
Why can I see it?

256
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:39,340
Let's go to the police first.

257
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:41,760
You have a single parent?

258
00:14:42,850 --> 00:14:43,460
I live with my dad.

259
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:44,580
Me too.

260
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:47,620
But my mom married my stepfather a long time ago.

261
00:14:47,910 --> 00:14:49,290
So my family doesn't feel like a single-parent one.

262
00:14:49,940 --> 00:14:51,280
What kind of person is your stepfather?

263
00:14:51,510 --> 00:14:52,310
He's very nice.

264
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:53,630
A poor guy.

265
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:54,550
A poor guy?

266
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,040
It's the same for him.

267
00:14:56,720 --> 00:14:58,260
My mother compares everything with others.

268
00:14:58,870 --> 00:14:59,770
What do you mean?

269
00:15:00,410 --> 00:15:02,550
-It's just… -Hello, readers.

270
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:05,860
The library is open until 10:00 today.

271
00:15:05,890 --> 00:15:06,550
It's so late.

272
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:10,460
Please don't forget your belongings when you leave.

273
00:15:11,020 --> 00:15:12,170
They're closing.

274
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:14,340
Where did you get that?

275
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:28,340
Why won't he read or reply to my message?

276
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:37,760
You can't get away with this.

277
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:39,540
I've called the police.

278
00:15:45,830 --> 00:15:47,500
Here comes the police. Tell them.

279
00:15:48,060 --> 00:15:49,230
I was talking about Chen Chuying.

280
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:50,910
Ms, did you call the police?

281
00:15:51,160 --> 00:15:51,680
Yes.

282
00:15:52,030 --> 00:15:52,760
I am the owner of the house.

283
00:15:53,400 --> 00:15:54,700
This man broke the lock of my door.

284
00:15:54,730 --> 00:15:55,450
He's a thief.

