00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,150
No, I'm not.

286
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:57,340
I didn't steal anything.

287
00:15:57,470 --> 00:15:58,290
Take him to the police station first.

288
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,560
Please cooperate with us.

289
00:15:59,940 --> 00:16:00,910
700, 700.

290
00:16:00,990 --> 00:16:01,920
705 calling.

291
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:03,020
700 responding.

292
00:16:03,510 --> 00:16:04,770
705 has arrived at the scene

293
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,570
and is in the process of understanding the situation.

294
00:16:06,730 --> 00:16:07,540
700. Roger that.

295
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,420
Are you Ms. Lin Jingmei?

296
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:21,180
Yes, I am.

297
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:23,120
Can you come with us to the police station?

298
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:25,850
I'm the one who reported the case.

299
00:16:26,930 --> 00:16:27,960
It's about a different case.

300
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,230
We have a few questions to confirm with you.

301
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:34,970
Would you be too preconceived?

302
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,470
He kept mentioning Xie He'an

303
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:39,530
and thanking Xie Hui for his help in the workplace.

304
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:41,850
He was so angry even about

305
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:42,760
the doll He Shoutang put in the window.

306
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:44,500
He's so emotional.

307
00:16:44,530 --> 00:16:46,040
He talked about everything else but that person.

308
00:16:46,890 --> 00:16:47,960
The moment Xie Hui mentioned her,

309
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:49,760
the topic was led somewhere else.

310
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,150
Now I think

311
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:55,960
that makes sense.

312
00:16:56,630 --> 00:16:57,730
Was he trying to conceal it?

313
00:17:01,060 --> 00:17:02,480
If you won't do it now,

314
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:04,109
we'll come back tomorrow

315
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,440
and can take you there.

316
00:17:05,780 --> 00:17:06,470
Or

317
00:17:06,970 --> 00:17:08,980
we can also come to your store during the day tomorrow.

318
00:17:27,300 --> 00:17:29,710
You're done with the art store for 2015.

319
00:17:30,220 --> 00:17:32,200
Why did you have so much money coming in 2016?

320
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,330
At that time, I was ready to open a store.

321
00:17:39,380 --> 00:17:40,840
My husband and my mother both

322
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:42,780
invested in it.

323
00:17:44,420 --> 00:17:45,000
Cash?

324
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:48,100
I guess so.

325
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:51,400
They don't have so much money now,

326
00:17:52,150 --> 00:17:53,760
not to mention at that time.

327
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:57,970
What do you mean?

328
00:17:59,910 --> 00:18:01,130
Your mother said so.

329
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:03,430
I don't think your mother would provide you with capital

330
00:18:03,690 --> 00:18:05,510
from the way she acted.

331
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:08,370
Besides, your husband's previous job as a salesman

332
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,600
wasn't successful.

333
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:11,560
He had no savings.

334
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:12,680
He couldn't just

335
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:14,350
provide 300,000 to 400,000 yuan,

336
00:18:15,050 --> 00:18:16,110
and not by remittance.

337
00:18:16,540 --> 00:18:17,300
It was cash.

338
00:18:18,710 --> 00:18:19,760
Do you want to think again

339
00:18:20,380 --> 00:18:21,620
where the deposits made one after another,

340
00:18:21,620 --> 00:18:23,180
adding up to almost three million yuan,

341
00:18:23,180 --> 00:18:23,990
come from?

342
00:18:32,810 --> 00:18:33,480
Excuse me.

343
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:36,440
Is it a crime to not remember what happened six years ago?

344
00:18:37,890 --> 00:18:38,760
I'm already very cooperative

345
00:18:38,780 --> 00:18:40,830
in answering these questions.

346
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,320
Besides, I'm the one who suffered from shoplifting.

347
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:46,100
Instead of asking the thief,

348
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:48,050
you're here asking me about something that happened long ago.

349
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:51,380
Ms. Lin, I'm sorry.

350
00:18:52,210 --> 00:18:54,100
What happened to your store is already being handled.

351
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:56,000
But there are still a few things

352
00:18:56,020 --> 00:18:56,820
we want you to clarify.

353
00:18:58,220 --> 00:18:58,830
So

354
00:18:59,590 --> 00:19:00,390
I hope you'll understand.

355
00:19:11,470 --> 00:19:12,410
So now...

356
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:16,550
Yes.

357
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:18,700
I think his mental condition…

358
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:20,240
He talks to the air

359
00:19:21,630 --> 00:19:22,130
No.

360
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,830
No stolen property on him.

361
00:19:23,860 --> 00:19:25,040
There is no property missing from the shop.

362
00:19:26,150 --> 00:19:26,490
Yes.

363
00:19:27,170 --> 00:19:27,620
I'm sure.

364
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:29,240
It's…

365
00:19:30,150 --> 00:19:31,640
Good.

366
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:32,520
Thank you, prosecutor.

367
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:34,670
You can go now.

368
00:19:35,770 --> 00:19:36,330
Why?

369
00:19:38,660 --> 00:19:39,830
Why what?

370
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,150
You like talking to the prosecutor, don't you?

371
00:19:42,970 --> 00:19:43,490
No.

372
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:45,570
That's all?

373
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:48,740
You broke into a store. It's trespassing.

374
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:49,780
No trial without complaint.

375
00:19:51,090 --> 00:19:51,590
I don't understand.

376
00:19:52,210 --> 00:19:53,770
That is, if the other party files a lawsuit,

377
00:19:53,800 --> 00:19:56,080
you'll still have to appear in court to go through the judicial process.

378
00:19:56,330 --> 00:19:57,590
You can't just leave today and be fine.

379
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:00,510
Then I'll be fine this way?

380
00:20:13,520 --> 00:20:14,540
Is this the same as yours?

381
00:20:24,400 --> 00:20:25,900
Why don't you answer the phone?

382
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,020
And your mother still thinks you're at my house

383
00:20:29,470 --> 00:20:30,240
Forget about it.

384
00:20:30,260 --> 00:20:31,170
What's this hairpin?

385
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:34,480
It's a good thing she still has something from elementary school.

386
00:20:35,410 --> 00:20:36,990
Hello, readers.

387
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:38,430
It's so late.

388
00:20:43,050 --> 00:20:44,000
They're closing up.

389
00:20:45,710 --> 00:20:46,480
Where did you get that?

390
00:20:49,690 --> 00:20:51,030
Was it a hairpin?

391
00:20:52,770 --> 00:20:53,730
How do you know?

392
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,920
A friend of mine from elementary school

393
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:57,680
wore it every day.

394
00:20:59,340 --> 00:21:01,510
How did you know it was a hairpin?

395
00:21:03,010 --> 00:21:04,090
My friend has a similar one.

396
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:07,550
Is your friend's name Xie He'an?

397
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:09,910
No.

398
00:21:11,900 --> 00:21:12,500
No.

399
00:21:14,630 --> 00:21:16,910
Anyway, I thought this was pretty when I was a kid.

400
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,480
Since it's a pair,

401
00:21:18,690 --> 00:21:19,860
I asked her for one.

402
00:21:21,190 --> 00:21:22,130
But she said

403
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:23,350
her mother made her this.

404
00:21:23,380 --> 00:21:24,140
She couldn't give it to me.

405
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:25,660
Then why do you have it?

406
00:21:26,750 --> 00:21:29,030
Actually, I forgot about this.

407
00:21:30,190 --> 00:21:31,090
But I can vaguely recall it.

408
00:21:31,130 --> 00:21:32,570
I think I found it at our house.

409
00:21:33,640 --> 00:21:35,230
She didn't come to our house.

410
00:21:35,710 --> 00:21:36,650
What happened to your friend?

411
00:21:37,390 --> 00:21:38,890
My mom said she changed schools.

412
00:21:39,570 --> 00:21:40,920
What's your friend's last name?

413
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:42,620
Maybe she changed her name.

414
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:46,610
Didn't your mother say anything when she saw you wearing this?

415
00:21:47,350 --> 00:21:48,100
I didn't wear it.

416
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:50,490
How could I let her see this?

417
00:21:51,020 --> 00:21:52,590
She forbids me to ask people for things.

418
00:21:53,710 --> 00:21:55,750
And I've always liked the decoration,

419
00:21:56,140 --> 00:21:56,810
not the hairpin.

420
00:21:57,380 --> 00:21:59,410
Isn't there a class in home economics called

421
00:21:59,450 --> 00:22:00,760
“Reusing Costume Resources”?

422
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:02,630
I did it in that class.

423
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:05,590
This is evidence, right?

424
00:22:06,540 --> 00:22:06,950
Yeah.

425
00:22:07,410 --> 00:22:08,460
Can we use this to arrest her?

426
00:22:09,030 --> 00:22:10,490
If I could, I would have shown her

427
00:22:10,510 --> 00:22:11,640
the picture of the hairpin.

428
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:13,010
I was afraid she would grab it when she came back.

429
00:22:15,780 --> 00:22:16,850
Anyway, we're continuing to investigate

430
00:22:16,850 --> 00:22:18,510
her unidentified assets.

431
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:20,940
I think

432
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:22,770
it's right.

433
00:22:24,290 --> 00:22:25,000
Where's Lin Jingmei?

434
00:22:26,650 --> 00:22:27,500
She was just released.

435
00:23:30,370 --> 00:23:31,630
What do you want?

436
00:23:56,430 --> 00:23:57,330
Why did you throw it away?

437
00:24:03,340 --> 00:24:04,690
Her mother can't even see

438
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:08,810
what her child looks like when she grows up.

439
00:24:09,580 --> 00:24:10,320
It's you again.

440
00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:12,460
Since you can't steal it, do you want to rob it now?

441
00:25:31,980 --> 00:25:33,330
Auntie Mei.

442
00:26:03,630 --> 00:26:04,660
What can she do to her?

443
00:26:46,800 --> 00:26:47,820
I am Lin Jingmei.

444
00:27:07,890 --> 00:27:09,170
Mr. Xie Hui said

445
00:27:09,820 --> 00:27:10,730
he'd go to identify and confirm

446
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:11,660
the body first.

447
00:27:11,930 --> 00:27:13,480
You just have to decide whether you want a biological identification.

448
00:27:15,410 --> 00:27:15,920
Be careful.

449
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:20,110
I think we…

450
00:27:48,190 --> 00:27:48,990
Mr. Xie.

451
00:28:04,880 --> 00:28:05,700
Ms. He, be careful.

452
00:28:58,160 --> 00:28:59,160
Xie He'an.

453
00:29:01,670 --> 00:29:02,580
We're going home.

454
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:31,710
Do you know what this is?

455
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:38,820
Yes, I do now.

456
00:29:42,100 --> 00:29:43,260
It's your daughter Lin Xin's.

457
00:29:43,870 --> 00:29:45,290
Of course, the original owner was her friend

458
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,270
Xie He'an.

459
00:29:48,650 --> 00:29:50,720
I forbade her to

460
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:53,720
ask He'an for it.

461
00:29:55,170 --> 00:29:55,670
Why not?

462
00:29:58,180 --> 00:30:00,330
Isn't it shameful to ask for something?

463
00:30:02,770 --> 00:30:04,500
Kids ask each other for things they like.

464
00:30:04,530 --> 00:30:05,750
There's no shame in that.

465
00:30:06,490 --> 00:30:07,500
It's shameful for adults to get what they want

466
00:30:07,530 --> 00:30:08,700
with terrible tricks.

467
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:16,620
Your daughter didn't ask for this.

468
00:30:17,410 --> 00:30:18,800
She found it at home.

469
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:36,110
I didn't kill Xie He'an.

470
00:30:46,250 --> 00:30:46,810
Xin.

471
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:49,210
I took the afternoon off and I'll be back around 3:00.

472
00:30:49,440 --> 00:30:50,730
I've already told Ms. He.

473
00:30:51,500 --> 00:30:51,930
Okay.

474
00:31:08,320 --> 00:31:08,900
What the heck?

475
00:31:16,270 --> 00:31:18,650
It's really beautiful in blue.

476
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,310
What about the roof?

477
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,220
You're stealing?

478
00:31:24,130 --> 00:31:25,310
Auntie Mei.

479
00:31:29,030 --> 00:31:30,770
These are all things from the store, aren't they?

480
00:31:33,370 --> 00:31:34,870
It's okay.

481
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:38,230
Who were you talking to?

482
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:41,360
Is Lin Xin here too?

483
00:31:42,420 --> 00:31:44,780
No, she doesn't know this place.

484
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:47,790
How long are you going to play?

485
00:31:48,610 --> 00:31:49,570
It's dangerous to be here alone,

486
00:31:49,610 --> 00:31:50,910
you know?

487
00:31:52,170 --> 00:31:54,820
I want to take this back after I finish it.

488
00:31:56,940 --> 00:31:58,680
It's old and dirty.

489
00:31:59,310 --> 00:32:00,420
Your mother won't allow it.

490
00:32:01,290 --> 00:32:02,190
Your mother

491
00:32:02,220 --> 00:32:05,170
will make you an expensive and beautiful dollhouse

492
00:32:05,820 --> 00:32:06,980
with many

493
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:09,390
miniature porcelain furniture inside.

494
00:32:10,220 --> 00:32:10,780
Yes.

495
00:32:10,810 --> 00:32:12,530
She already made it for me.

496
00:32:22,620 --> 00:32:25,000
Did Lin Xin ask you

497
00:32:25,870 --> 00:32:26,670
for a hairpin before?

498
00:32:27,290 --> 00:32:28,860
I asked my mom.

499
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,760
But she didn't want me to give it to others.

500
00:32:33,470 --> 00:32:34,010
Okay.

501
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:45,350
Auntie Mei, close the door for me.

502
00:32:46,910 --> 00:32:49,500
Close the door for me.

503
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,520
It can be closed.

504
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:00,530
Just right.

505
00:33:03,750 --> 00:33:05,120
It's so beautiful here.

506
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:32,360
-I was thinking... -Sorry.

507
00:33:32,710 --> 00:33:34,390
I don't feel well.

508
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:35,960
I need to go to the bathroom.

509
00:33:36,620 --> 00:33:37,700
Are you okay, Jingmei?

510
00:35:16,190 --> 00:35:17,060
What nonsense!

511
00:35:17,680 --> 00:35:19,200
She still claimed she didn't kill her.

512
00:35:19,990 --> 00:35:21,360
It's like asking for ransom after the hostage is dead.

513
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:27,100
Would that kill her?

514
00:35:29,070 --> 00:35:31,280
If she was extremely nervous because of fear,

515
00:35:31,470 --> 00:35:32,740
she might hyperventilate.

516
00:35:34,020 --> 00:35:36,310
And she was locked up in such a small, confined space,

517
00:35:37,650 --> 00:35:39,590
if she breathed in too much carbon dioxide…

518
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:44,820
Why?

519
00:35:46,250 --> 00:35:47,190
Just for a hairpin?

520
00:35:47,970 --> 00:35:48,700
Because she didn't like it.

521
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:51,910
She didn't like a kid?

522
00:35:53,640 --> 00:35:54,490
He Shoutang.

523
00:35:55,150 --> 00:35:55,860
The art store.

524
00:35:57,070 --> 00:35:59,210
Xie Hui's college student colleague.

525
00:36:01,300 --> 00:36:02,210
Maybe even the customers.

526
00:36:03,780 --> 00:36:04,460
Everything.

527
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:07,340
I don't understand.

528
00:36:13,310 --> 00:36:14,930
There is something others have but you don't.

529
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:17,360
You want it so much

530
00:36:19,230 --> 00:36:20,650
that you even start to resent

531
00:36:20,690 --> 00:36:21,570
the person who has it.

532
00:36:23,970 --> 00:36:24,940
You have these moments too, right?

533
00:36:25,570 --> 00:36:26,040
Jealousy.

534
00:36:31,450 --> 00:36:31,860
You've experienced it, right?

535
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:35,040
Others are jealous of me.

536
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:40,350
Anyway,

537
00:36:43,030 --> 00:36:43,930
this is what she said.

538
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:48,160
Just because she mastered some handicrafts,

539
00:36:49,510 --> 00:36:51,120
she could open a beautiful store,

540
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,600
selling something of no use.

541
00:36:55,330 --> 00:36:56,890
It was just because her husband could make money.

542
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,750
And what's her name, the college student,

543
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,900
she changed her boyfriends all the time.

544
00:37:01,070 --> 00:37:03,800
Her living expenses and tuition fees were paid by the family.

545
00:37:07,280 --> 00:37:08,890
This store

546
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:11,330
is just a hobby and accomplishment to them.

547
00:37:11,760 --> 00:37:13,880
It's just the money of a pack of popcorn when going to see a movie.

548
00:37:18,870 --> 00:37:20,010
Those who

549
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:22,090
work harder

550
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:23,480
should get the benefits, don't they?

551
00:37:24,570 --> 00:37:26,740
Even to Zhao Baisi, who was pursuing her, she…

552
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:29,710
Mei.

553
00:37:31,180 --> 00:37:32,040
This is my colleague.

554
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:33,120
Zhao Baisi.

555
00:37:34,070 --> 00:37:34,710
-Hello. -Hello.

556
00:37:34,740 --> 00:37:36,320
This is Ms. Lin Jingmi.

557
00:37:37,030 --> 00:37:37,690
Ms. Lin.

558
00:37:43,440 --> 00:37:43,980
Thank you, Hui.

559
00:37:44,490 --> 00:37:46,010
I'll go find a place to put it first.

560
00:37:48,110 --> 00:37:48,890
Hello, Ms. Lin.

561
00:37:49,710 --> 00:37:50,120
Hello.

562
00:37:51,680 --> 00:37:53,960
[Businessman Zhao Baisi]

563
00:37:52,900 --> 00:37:55,080
Xie Hui is my boss.

564
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:56,890
He takes good care of me.

565
00:38:00,620 --> 00:38:01,430
I'll go on ahead.

566
00:38:01,670 --> 00:38:02,290
Yes, please.

567
00:38:03,820 --> 00:38:04,820
She didn't even notice

568
00:38:04,850 --> 00:38:06,500
